---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '../components/Breadcrumb.astro';
import CTABanner from '../components/CTABanner.astro';

const personSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Person",
  "name": "Patricia Azevedo",
  "jobTitle": "European Travel Consultant",
  "worksFor": {
    "@type": "Organization",
    "name": "DURIAN Travel",
    "url": "https://www.duriantravel.com"
  },
  "url": "https://www.duriantravel.com/patricia-azevedo/",
  "description": "Patricia Azevedo is a European travel consultant who helps non-European travelers plan trips to Europe — from Schengen visa strategy to full itinerary design. She founded DURIAN Travel after years of navigating European travel personally and professionally.",
  "knowsAbout": [
    "Schengen visa applications",
    "European travel planning",
    "Itinerary design for non-European travelers",
    "Multi-country Europe routes",
    "Travel insurance for Schengen",
    "Cross-regional travel logistics"
  ],
  "areaServed": "Worldwide"
};
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Patricia Azevedo | European Travel Consultant · DURIAN Travel"
  description="Meet Patricia Azevedo, the consultant behind DURIAN Travel. She helps non-European travelers worldwide plan smarter Europe trips — visa strategy, itinerary design, and everything in between."
  canonical="https://www.duriantravel.com/patricia-azevedo/"
  breadcrumb={[{ name: 'Patricia Azevedo', url: 'https://www.duriantravel.com/patricia-azevedo/' }]}
  schema={personSchema}
  keywords="Patricia Azevedo, European travel consultant, DURIAN Travel founder, Schengen visa strategy, Europe itinerary planning"
>
  <div class="container">
    <Breadcrumb items={[{ name: 'Meet Patricia Azevedo' }]} />
  </div>

  <section class="hero-sm hero-gradient">
    <div class="container container--narrow">
      <span class="section-label" style="color:var(--color-accent-light)">Founder</span>
      <h1 class="hero-sm__title" style="color:white">Meet Patricia Azevedo</h1>
      <p class="hero-sm__subtitle">
        European travel consultant. Founder of DURIAN Travel. The person who answers your emails.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container container--narrow prose">
      <p>
        If you have tried to plan a trip to Europe from outside the continent, you already know the problem. The information exists, but it is scattered across embassy websites, forums, blog posts, and advice written for audiences who never need to think about visas at all.
      </p>
      <p>
        That gap is what Patricia built DURIAN to fill.
      </p>

      <h2>How this started</h2>
      <p>
        Patricia did not set out to become a travel consultant. She started where most people do: planning her own trips to Europe, running into questions that did not have clear answers, and slowly turning personal trial-and-error into something more systematic.
      </p>
      <p>
        Over years of travel and research, she learned how visa requirements change by embassy, how itinerary structure shapes an application, and how small documentation choices can make a file feel either credible or fragile. She began helping people in her network with their first Europe trips. Eventually that grew into DURIAN Travel.
      </p>

      <h2>What she does</h2>
      <p>
        Patricia works on two connected problems: <strong>Schengen visa strategy</strong> and <strong>Europe itinerary planning</strong>. In practice, these are rarely separate. The route determines the embassy. The embassy changes the document emphasis. The budget changes the story your bank statements and bookings have to support.
      </p>
      <p>
        She reviews document packages, flags what is missing or weak before submission, and helps clients build a stronger application narrative. She also designs routes that make sense for budget, pacing, and the realities of getting to Europe from places as different as Sao Paulo, Nairobi, Seoul, Sydney, or Mexico City.
      </p>
      <p>
        She has worked with travelers from Latin America, North America, Asia, Africa, and Australia, and her own travel experience spans Western, Northern, Central, and Eastern Europe.
      </p>

      <h2>A few things worth knowing</h2>
      <ul class="check-list">
        <li><strong>She is not a visa agency.</strong> DURIAN helps clients understand and strengthen the process, but does not submit applications on their behalf.</li>
        <li><strong>She is not a lawyer.</strong> If a case needs legal advice, Patricia will say so clearly.</li>
        <li><strong>She responds personally.</strong> When you contact DURIAN, you are talking to Patricia, not a sales team or outsourced inbox.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Working with Patricia</h2>
      <p>
        The best starting point is usually the <a href="/free-visa-audit/">Free Visa Audit</a>, where Patricia reviews your situation and tells you exactly what to do next. If you already know what kind of support you need, head to the <a href="/services/">service packages</a>. If you have a question first, <a href="/contact/">get in touch</a>.
      </p>

      <div class="notice notice--info" style="margin-top:var(--space-7)">
        <span aria-hidden="true">ℹ️</span>
        <span>Last updated: April 2026.</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CTABanner />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
.hero-sm { padding-block: var(--space-16); }
.hero-sm__title {
  font-size: clamp(var(--text-2xl), 4vw, var(--text-4xl));
  margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
}
.hero-sm__subtitle {
  font-size: var(--text-lg);
  color: hsl(150 30% 75%);
  max-width: 60ch;
  line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
}
</style>
